  "texts": [
    "We find DrC C [β]ψ = Dr D D [id X 1 ⊗•••⊗X λ ⊗ β ⊗ id X λ+m+1 ⊗•••⊗Xn]ψ by comparing boundary conditions and the morphism at the anchor point.",
    "That is,Dr C C [β]ψ = m κ=1 d Yκ m κ=1 d X κ+λ 1/2 σ -1 D                                   = Dr D D [id X 1 ⊗•••⊗X λ ⊗ β ⊗ id X λ+m+1 ⊗•••⊗Xn]ψ.",
    "Since the operator DrD D [id X 1 ⊗•••⊗X λ ⊗ β ⊗ id X λ+m+1 ⊗•••⊗Xn] annihilates the orthogonal comple- ment of P (X 1,•••,Xn) D, this proves the lemma.",
    "□ LinksA link is a finite dual path L = (f 1, • • •, f l) consisting of at least five faces, such that• f i and f j share an edge if and only if j = i ± 1 (or i = j).",
    "In particular, L is self-avoiding.• the first four faces of L lie on a straight line, as do the last four faces of L.The initial puncture of L is the edge e i =: ∂ i L ∈ E between faces f 1 and f 2 and the final puncture of L is the edge e f =: ∂ f L between faces f l-1 and f l.To a link L we associate a region C L consisting of all vertices and edges belonging to the faces constituting the link except for the initial and final punctures e i, e f, and all the faces f 3, • • •, f l-2, which we call the bulk faces of the link."
  ]
